Package net.neto_framework.server.event.events

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ServerClientConnect
    An event that is fired when a new client successfully connects.
    ServerFailedToAcceptConnection
    An event that is fired when the server fails to accept a TCP or UDP connection.
    ServerInvalidPacket
    An event that is fired when the server receives an invalid packet id or packet.
    ServerPacketException
    An event that is fired when the server has a problem receiving or sending a packet.
    ServerReceiveInvalidHandshake
    An event that is fired when the server receives an invalid handshake packet.
    ServerStart
    An event that is fired when the server starts.
    ServerStop
    An event that is fired when the server stops.
